[l] Wie krasser Bullshit sind Medikamenten-Ablaufdaten? Ziemlicher Bullshit, wie sich rausstellt.The dates on drug labels are simply the point up to which the Food and Drug Administration and pharmaceutical companies guarantee their effectiveness, typically at two or three years. But the dates don’t necessarily mean they’re ineffective immediately after they “expire” — just that there’s no incentive for drugmakers to study whether they could still be usable.
